  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "16. And herein—On this account, accordingly; that is, looking forward to that awful day (compare 2Co 5:10).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I exercise myself—The \"I\" here is emphatic; \"Whatever they do, this is my study.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to have always a conscience void of offence, &c.—See Ac 23:1; 2Co 1:12; 2:17, &c.; that is, \"These are the great principles of my life and conduct—how different from turbulence and sectarianism!\"",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
